      "id": "rotterdam_safety_guide.md-1",
      "text": "Dial **0900-0101** (confidential emotional and legal guidance for victims of harassment or assault). ## Dutch Street Harassment Laws - **Street Harassment Bylaws (Rotterdam APV):** Under local municipal regulations, street harassment (catcalling, hissing, following, or blocking paths in public spaces) is an offense. Fines up to €340 can be issued by municipal law enforcement officers (BOAs) or police. - **Stalking and Intimidation (Dutch Penal Code Article 285b):** Systematically following, contacting, or hovering near a person to force them to do or tolerate something, or to cause fear, is recognized as stalking (belaging). Stalking carries penalties of up to 3 years in prison or hefty criminal fines. ## Safety Best Practices - **Codeword Activation:** If you feel you are being followed, open",
